Automatic Data Processing, Inc. Awarded Human Capital Management Services Contract By City of Reno, Nevada
Thursday, 12 Jul 2012 08:00am EDT
Automatic Data Processing, Inc. announced that it has signed a five-year contract with the City of Reno, Nevada, for human capital management (HCM) services in support of 1500 city employees. The Company is working with Reno government officials to design and implement an integrated HCM solution that will streamline and automate a majority of its core functions to help enhance the overall efficiencies of the city's human resources department. The Company will deliver a broad spectrum of HCM services, including human resources, payroll processing, time and labor management, benefits administration, COBRA and flexible spending accounts.Â 
